republican /rɪˈpʌblɪkən/

(republicans) 

1. ADJ Republican means relating to a republic. In republican systems of government, power is held by the people or the representatives that they elect. 共和的 

例： ...the nations that had adopted the republican form of government. …采用了共和制政体的国家。 

2. ADJ If someone is Republican , they belong to or support the Republican Party. 共和党的 

例： Lower taxes made Republican voters happier with their party. 更低的税率使共和党选民对该党更加满意。 

3. N-COUNT A Republican is someone who supports or belongs to the Republican Party. 共和党人 

例： What made you decide to become a Republican, as opposed to a Democrat? 是什么使你决定成为共和党人，而不是民主党人呢？

